column1: OSF | Wave 8.2.2 | ACC1 | IT | DSL orders not getting 1290 (FINAL) after 1286 ORDER_POSITION_FINAL in COM
column38:
Hi Team,
We have observed DSL orders are getting stuck at 1286 (ORDER_POSITION_FINAL ) and not moving ahead to 1290 (Final) state.

Test Data:
Barcode: *VDE5601835746*

Step to reproduce:
1. Login to Omnius (Tele/ retail ) agent
2. Place DSL order
3. Submit the order to Backend
4. Complete Backend process
5. After completing Backend Order will stuck at 1286
6. You will observe order will not reach 1290 (FINAL)

Expected Result: 
Orders should get 1290 (Final)

Actual Result:
Orders not getting 1290 (Final) and stuck at 1286 (Order_Position_Final)
column221: DSL orders not getting Final and it is not reflecting complted success on FE
column466: ITPOSDB was down due to CRQ activity and it wasn't coming up after that, so IDBA Team manually started the DB.
column770: 11/Jun/24 1:04 PM;akash.ubbu@vodafone.com;Issue is resolved now, orders are moving ahead to 1290;;;

column1: OSF | ACC3 | Wave 8.2.3 | Regression | Service Address check with Auto suggestion is not working as expected
column38:
While performing Service availability check we are unable to perform the service check with the auto suggestion.

where previously we able to search with this format -- - 81927 Munchen gottfried 15 ---

and address search was working but

now since tuesday 14th May we have to enter addresses in detail -- 81927 munchen gottfried-benn-str. 15 

 

And if we are missing any single character to add we get error "No Address Found"

 

Steps to Reproduce:

1) Login to Telesales/ Retail and perform Service availability check

2) enter address in format : 81927 - Munchen- Gottfried- 15 this will give error  and 

using this format 81927 - Munchen - Gottfried-benn-str.-15 this will work 

 

Expected Result:

Only entering 81927 - Munchen- Gottfried- 15 should also give the result of address without auto suggestion.

 

Actual Result:

currently we have to use the detailed address to search the same. and if we are missing any single character we are getting error as "NO Address Found"

[~gokul.vade@vodafone.com]  [~ajay.bhavar@vodafone.com]

this ACC tracking Bug can now be retestet on ACC1 with the *+2nd scenario+* ->{+}{+}no Insurance option should be visible(see description below)

Existing customers on ACC1 they can be used for the retest:
|Customer ID|Subscriber Number|Tariff Option|SOC|
|104724208|GSM1738852612|GM1LH30 |24HATAV17|
|110016580|GSM1726591197|GM1MH40 |24HATAV17|
|107241788|GSM1792332596|GM1LH40 |24HATAV17|
|104058520|GSM1727077848|SMART3XXL|24HATAV17|

 

*(*)New Change(*)*

*+1st scenario:+*

SOC “sales expired” -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is no longer offered + Vodafone device, which was purchased no longer than 120 days ago

Expected result: Customer can book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = true)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase <120 days) & tariff + legacy(or Cover or Cover Plus) SOC “sales expired” = true

 

*+2nd scenario:+*

SOC “sales expired”, but device too old -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is no longer offered, + Vodafone device, which was purchased more than 120 days ago

Expected result: User cannot book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = true)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase >120 days) & tariff + Legacy/Cover/CoverPlus SOC “sales expired” = true

 

*+3rd scenario:+*

SOC NOT sales expired -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is still offered + Vodafone device, which was purchased no longer than 120 days ago

Expected result: User cannot book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = false)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase <120 days) & tariff + legacy/Cover/CoverPlus SOC “sales expired” = false

 

*+4th scenario:+*

SOC NOT sales expired, but device too old -> user with existing Legacy/Cover/Cover Plus insurance, which is still offered + Vodafone device, which was purchased more than 120 days ago.

Expected result: User cannot book VC and VCP (with SOC “sales expired” = false)

Required existing customer: Contract with HW (purchase >120 days) & tariff + legacy/Cover/CoverPlus SOC “sales expired” = false

 ;;;

I see this use case where there is no hardware selected ( Mobile Hardware) in the screenshot.

Also there is no change for IMEI. IMEI should be captured manually either cart contains HW or NO HW. It has no relation with HW / tariff. This field has to be captured for both type of insurance products VODAFONE_COVER and VODAFONE_COVER_PLUS

column1: OSF | ACC1 | In Cable address new acquisition of KUD standalone via telesales is blocked as IBAN validation is not working as expected
column38:
In unity address new acquisition of KUD standalone via telesales is blocked.

*Steps to recreate:*

1)Place a new order in Telesales in NRW or KBW region.
2) Select a KUD Standalone product
3) Fill all the necessary details in the checkout region.

{*}In Billing section, click card symbol Enter Bank account number and sort code{*}, IBAN validation is OK, SEPA is OK
4) Try to complete the order -> but error message says its foreign bank account which is not the case
column97: 07/Jun/23 12:57 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;IBAN validation not working with bank code and sort code.docx;https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/secure/attachment/1073116/IBAN+validation+not+working+with+bank+code+and+sort+code.docx
column221: Its not possible to book KUD products for both VKD and Unity in case IBAN validation is not working as expected -> copy & pase in of IBAN should help
column466:
When we click on creditcard symbol on the right and  enter details like bank account number , it automatically creates IBAN and prefills it.
In this particular scenerio, logic to identify IBAN country check was not working because in this case IBAN is prefilling through creditcard symbol automatically.
So enhanced the logic to identify if the prefilled IBAN is germen IBAN or no so that residencecheck behaviour can be accordingly handled.

column810:
17/Aug/23 2:36 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~singireddy.reddy@vodafone.com] [~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com] 

 
Alexandra Vaduva added a comment -
 
 
Hi Harsha/Ari,

This was clear from the beginning, yes, but as I mentioned, the implementation was intended to be like this :

*In case of telesales, if sepa is true, then this check will be shown and the flow is blocked → agent is not able to continue*

Which means that it does *NOT* matter _what IBAN is used_ , this will be shown if the sepa is true and *If the KUD product is part of cable_app_de category .* 

I agree that the way this is working is not consistent : in one case the agent is able to continue but in another the agent is not able to continue.

The final question is - when should the agent be able to continue the checkout process and when should the agent be blocked? According to the initial documentation the agent should not be able to continue and according to these comments the agent should be able to continue .

What is the purpose of this error message and what was wrongly implemented exactly? We can implement a fix according to these comments but we need to know if the issue is that the whole implementation was not done correctly or not, in order to fix the actual issue and not just a particular case .;;;

We have analyzed further and found that there is recent requirement over (https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-690) [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/epic.svg!VFDED1FTS-5531: CR780 - Change of payment validation check for existing SEPA mandatIN DESIGN|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-5531] which is now available as part of the software where we are testing the above scenario.

As part the requirement we are now showing NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button of payment section if the scenario we are performing meets below conditions.

System will validate if payment method = "direct debit"
 * if yes: system will validate if IBAN = DE-IBAN

 ** if yes: system will validate if bank account owner (payer contact) = legal contact

 *** if yes: the system will validate if the bank account owner address (payer address) = legal address

 **** if yes: the system switches to the next checkout section

 **** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 *** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 ** if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button

 * if no: SHOW NOTIFICATION MODAL and disable "Weiter" button.

column1: OSF | Wave7.1 | ACC1&ACC2 | Telesales | Unitymedia orders with manual approval do not reach status completed
column38:
In case unitymedia order is not approved automatically in RNS, we are missing the order status and customer number in OSF.

Steps:
 * start order for unitymedia in Telesales (e.g. with KIP)
 * Submit order and check weborder ID in IAV
 * Identify reference ID is created in unity backend but order is not approved automatically
 * Approve order with the given reference ID in unitymedia backend (No new order is created! Weborder ID is set as external reference)
 * Check status / customer number in VKD and OGW -> information for customer ID is missing and status is not completed

Expected:

Also for manual approved orders the status is set to completed and customer ID is transferred via VKD to OSF

column857:
07/Dec/23 1:51 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Updates:

 

OGW needs the customer number in case Unity Manual Approval Orders in Telesales and Retails, which should be provided from VKD to OGW within the existing FulfillmentStarted Request.

 

The customer number is atm provided only for Auto Approval Orders, but missing for Manual Approval orders, therefore the document cannot be archived and the OGW processing remain in status pending (the VKD status is SUCCESS but the orders don't get Sucecss status in OSF Fronend):

An error was encountered while invoking ScanView-SaveDocument WS. Details [Error_Code: HTTPOutbound_0001, Error_Message: Received a fault from processing server for service '/ScanView-001/SaveDocument': An invalid number format or number value was encountered.

Note: Retail Manual Approval Orders don't have this issue because the call to oneDMS/Customernumber is not needed for the E2E flow. They get the Status Success.

 

As the customer number has not been sent for Manual Approval Order until now, a new PST change is required.

I will take the topic with me and check if we can request this change at the PST CAT train, Team Ash(Benjamin Sachse) or Nora.

 

The new requirement should contain following information:
 * no difference between retail and telesales from cable perspective
 * example set status messages received by OSF
 * fulfilment started from manual approval 
 * fulfilment started from automatic approval 


 * explanation on
 * what you clicked to create the manual approval order
 * how to approve the manual approval order

Will update here once it is clear how to process with the new change.;;;
